<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Property Data Import Job Failed</title>
    <style>
      body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; }
      .header { background-color: #f8d7da; padding: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #dc3545; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .error-details { background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 4px; border-left: 3px solid #dc3545; }
      .error-message { font-family: monospace; background-color: #fff; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; }
      .footer { margin-top: 30px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-size: 12px; color: #6c757d; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="header">
      <h1>‚ùå Property Data Import Job Failed</h1>
      <p><strong>Timestamp:</strong> <%= @timestamp.strftime("%B %d, %Y at %I:%M %p %Z") %></p>
      <p><strong>Job Duration:</strong> <%= "%.2f" % @job_duration %> seconds (before failure)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="error-details">
      <h2>üî• Error Details</h2>
      <div class="error-message">
        <%= simple_format(@error_message) %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
      <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Immediate Actions Required</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Check the application logs for more detailed error information</li>
        <li>Verify the PCPA GIS service is accessible</li>
        <li>Check database connectivity and available disk space</li>
        <li>Review recent code changes that might have caused this failure</li>
        <li>Consider running the job manually to reproduce the issue</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
      <p>This email was automatically generated by the Property Data Import Job.<br>
      Please investigate this failure immediately to ensure data freshness.</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>